\int_0^\pi f(x)P(x) dx=0
\int_0^\pi f^2(x) dx = \int_0^\pi f^2(x) dx - \int_0^\pi f(x)P(x) dx = \\ \int_0^\pi f(x) (f(x) -  P(x) )dx\leq \int_0^\pi |f(x) (f(x) -  P(x) )|dx \\ \leq M \int_0^\pi |f(x) -  P(x) |dx \lt M\epsilon
\int_0^\pi f^2(x) dx  =0
